  <hint format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Hint 1 (Pre-switch Analysis):</strong> At DC steady state: inductor = short circuit, capacitor = open circuit. Use these to find \(V_0\) and \(I_0\). After switches flip, sources disconnect &mdash; source-free parallel RLC remains.</p>]]></text>
  </hint>
  <hint format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Hint 2 (Formulas):</strong> For parallel RLC natural response: \(\alpha = \frac{1}{2RC}\), \(\omega_0 = \frac{1}{\sqrt{LC}}\). Initial rate of change: \(\frac{dv_o}{dt}(0^+) = -\frac{1}{C}\!\left(\frac{V_0}{R} + I_0\right)\).</p>]]></text>
  </hint>
  <hint format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Hint 3 (Worked Step):</strong> For underdamped: \(v_o(t) = e^{-\alpha t}(B_1 \cos\omega_d t + B_2 \sin\omega_d t)\). From \(v_o(0^+) = B_1 = V_0\). Then: \(\frac{dv_o}{dt}(0^+) = -\alpha B_1 + \omega_d B_2\). Solve for \(B_2\).</p>]]></text>
  </hint>

